sections.text:
The sheriff or friend of the court shall disburse the wages or salary of an employed prisoner for only the following purposes in the order stated:

(a) Board of the prisoner;

(b) Necessary travel expense to and from work and other incidental expenses of the prisoner;

(c) Support of the prisoner's dependents, if any;

(d) Payment, either in full or ratably, of the prisoner's obligations, acknowledged by him in writing, or which have been reduced to judgment;

(e) The balance, if any, to the prisoner upon his discharge.

History:1962, Act 60, Eff. Mar. 28, 1963
